{"TopicId":190196,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"help setting up resonant orbits for comnet on mun","CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T08:00:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T08:00:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nusing this tool\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0i was able to set up a nearly perfect triangular orbit around kerbin, yet when trying to do the exact same thing on the mun i get different results, im not good at explaining things.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nim trying to set up a triangular constelation evenly spaced at 300,000 m, i do my burns according to that tool yet my relays end up in weird orbits, like, instead of it coming out to an equalateral triangle i keep getting an \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:16px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003Eisosceles.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\na picture to better explain myself, anybody know what im doing wrong? is the tool flawed? my first instinct says that my orbit is to low, but if i was higher up i would have the same results now that i think about it.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vMKprdB.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/vMKprdB.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T08:01:42Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 08:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by putnamto\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T08:08:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI followed this tutorial and got my relay network just perfect:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022173518\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4380329963\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/161180-tutorial-how-to-create-a-satellite-network-with-evenly-spaced-satellites/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaking sure the orbital period is exactly the same for all satellites is quite important to have a stable configuration, the individual altitudes can vary a bit, doesn\u0027t matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T08:28:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nholy fricking math batman\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T08:33:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if you want to have a perfect relay sat network, that\u0027s the way to go \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESave for the math, what I do step by step:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Decide what orbit altitude you want to go for, and if it should be a polar or equatorial orbit. Let\u0027s for example say, you want a 500km triangular\u00A0polar orbit constellation around Mun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n2. Build your rocket with three deployable relay antenna modules, which each should have a probe core, a battery, solar panels, a small fuel tank, and a small\u00A0engine.\u00A0Launch it, and bring it into a 500km polar orbit around Mun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n3. Check the resonant orbit values at\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#3d6594;\u0022\u003Ehttps://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0, the important data here are the orbital period of\u00A04h:0m:18.1s, and the altitude of the apoapsis of that resonant orbit which is\u00A0795.979km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n4. Deploy\u00A0your first antenna module, immediately go prograde with your main rocket and raise the apoapsis to\u00A0795.979km. I strongly suggest you orient your rocket to normal before deploying the antenna module to avoid potential collisions when raising the apoapsis after deployment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n5. Switch to the antenna module, enable the engine, and check the orbital period, which should be close to\u00A04h:0m:18.1s. If the orbital period is longer, go retrograde and burn slightly to adjust, if the orbital period is shorter, go prograde and\u00A0burn slightly to adjust. What is important here is to achieve the exact orbital period as close as possible, the actual values for apoapsis and periapsis are not that important (if you, for example, end up with a 505x492km orbit, that\u0027s perfectly fine).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n6. Switch to your main rocket and circularize at the next periapsis (which is 500km, of course).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n7. Continue with your 2nd antenna, same procedure as point 4 to 6\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n8.\u00A0Continue with your 3rd\u00A0antenna, same procedure as point 4 to 5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n9. Enjoy your triangular relay setup\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 style=\u0022border-style:none;vertical-align:middle;\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EBtw, another useful link I followed:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T11:27:19Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 11:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T08:40:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni didnt know about orbital periods and their importance, the stock game doesnt tell you that info as far as i know, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E does though.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nthanks guys\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T08:41:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock game does since 1.7, iirc, check the display in the lower left corner, there are a couple of buttons to change between different data to display. But if you\u0027re already using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E, you\u0027re more than fine, have all data at your fingertips. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223713995\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575621603\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks guys\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re welcome, happy to help. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T08:46:30Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 08:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T09:22:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell the one on the mun didnt turn out so well, going to scrap it and try again, but with my newfound knowledge i made this.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHAIL SATAN!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022xvQYFFa.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/xvQYFFa.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T09:34:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks\u00A0good, well done \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T09:40:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575624880\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks\u00A0good, well done \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin the last pic, their orbital periods are off by \u002B-5 minutes, but that shouldnt be cause for concern should it?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nand something i didnt notice is that the meyer resonant orbit calculator does days in a 24 hour format, and kerbins days are only 6 hours, i sat here scratching my head for a few minutes on that one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T09:42:00Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 09:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by putnamto\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T09:56:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714005\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575625255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin the last pic, their orbital periods are off by \u002B-5 minutes, but that shouldnt be cause for concern should it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, what fraction of the orbital period are those \u002B- 5 min? How many orbits does it take to completely mess up the formation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn other words: I\u0027d change the orbits so that they have the same orbital period down to as good as possible (e.g. one second?). (It doesn\u0027t matter so much if they have this period with identical AP and PE: as long as the period is identical they\u0027ll keep their relative positions.) You may want to lower the thrust limit of the engines on the satellites to do that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T09:59:32Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 09:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by AHHans\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T09:57:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714005\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575625255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin the last pic, their orbital periods are off by \u002B-5 minutes, but that shouldnt be cause for concern should it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, think about it: let\u0027s assume you play 10 years Kerbal time. The orbital period from my example is\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E4h:0m:18.1s. Let\u0027s assume that satellite\u0027s orbit is\u00A0off by 5 seconds.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E10 Years = 4260 days = 25560 hours = 6390 Orbits. So, after 10 years that one satellite\u0027s orbit would be off by 31950 seconds, or 8.8 hours or more than 2 whole orbits... not good.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EI try to be meticulously\u00A0precise up to the very last digit with the orbital periods, with the result that even after more than 30 years after deployment all my relay sat constellation still look like proper\u00A0equilateral triangles.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T09:59:29Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 09:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T09:59:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714013\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575626199\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, what fraction of the orbital period are those \u002B- 5 min? How many orbits does it take to completely mess up the formation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn other words: I\u0027d change the orbits so that they have the same orbital period down to at least one second. (It doesn\u0027t matter so much if they have this period with identical AP and PE: as long as the period is identical they\u0027ll keep their relative positions.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe orbital period on three of them is 34 days and 5 mins, on one its 34 days and 8 mins and on another its 34 days and 3 mins, i dont have time to continue playing the game, but ill see what i can do later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T10:04:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575626346\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe orbital period on three of them is 34 days and 5 mins, on one its 34 days and 8 mins and on another its 34 days and 3 mins\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, O.K. That means it\u0027ll take them about 20 years to move one tenth out of (relative-)position. \u003Cstrong\u003EI\u003C/strong\u003E would still try to correct that, but if that\u0027s fine for you then just leave it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T10:06:34Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 10:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by AHHans\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Efixed typo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T10:07:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714018\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575626691\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, O.K. That means it\u0027ll take them about 10 years to move one tenth out of (relative-)position. \u003Cstrong\u003EI\u003C/strong\u003E would still try to correct that, but if that\u0027s fine for you then just leave it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni am fine with that, but i have to ask, how did you come up with that? what was the math involved? im horrible at math, and i use alot of mods to get past that, but im curious and would like to learn.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nand im also a little dumb. i would ask you to draw me a picture if you could.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T10:23:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575626834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni am fine with that, but i have to ask, how did you come up with that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet\u0027s see:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n34 days and 8 mins and 34 days and 3 mins is a maximum difference of 5 min\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n34 days and 5 mins are:\u00A0 \u003Cem\u003E34 (days) * 6 (hours/day) * 60 (min/hour) \u002B 5 (min) = 12245 min\u003C/em\u003E for one orbit\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\ndeviation per orbit: \u003Cem\u003E5 min / 12245 min = ca. 0.00041\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\none tenth deviation in: \u003Cem\u003E0.1 / 0.00041 = 243.9\u003C/em\u003E orbits\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nin time units: \u003Cem\u003E243.9 (orbits) = 243.9 (orbits) * 34 (days/orbit) = 8292.6 (days) / ca. 400 (days/year) = ca. 20 years\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that last line is a rough estimate. A Kerbin year isn\u0027t exactly 400 days long, your orbits aren\u0027t exactly 34 days long, yada, yada, yada. Who cares? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575626834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni would ask you to draw me a picture if you could.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI probably could, but I\u0027m not going to! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T10:27:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575626834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni am fine with that, but i have to ask, how did you come up with that? what was the math involved?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee my example above or that from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/197939-ahhans/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022197939\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/197939-ahhans/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@AHHans\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0he posted a few minutes ago. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ELong story short: be as precise as possible, and the shorter the orbital period is, the more important becomes precision. It costs you only a few minutes, which is way less time than you\u0027ll need to rebuild a constellation every few Kerbin years.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T10:30:05Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 10:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T11:09:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575628023\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee my example above or that from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/197939-ahhans/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022197939\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/197939-ahhans/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@AHHans\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0he posted a few minutes ago. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ELong story short: be as precise as possible, and the shorter the orbital period is, the more important becomes precision. It costs you only a few minutes, which is way less time than you\u0027ll need to rebuild a constellation every few Kerbin years.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthats for sure, i did get my mun constelation looking good, but it turned into a little wile later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T12:20:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223714019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575626834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndraw me a picture if you could.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not any good at drawing as well, you\u0027d end up with a drawing similar to this, best case (found this one on the NASA website \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/nmp/ds1/img/top.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.jpl.nasa.gov/nmp/ds1/img/top.jpg\u003C/a\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022top.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002277.20\u0022 height=\u0022386\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/nmp/ds1/img/top.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T15:32:57Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 03:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T12:46:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223713985\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575619202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nusing this tool\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0i was able to set up a nearly perfect triangular orbit around kerbin, yet when trying to do the exact same thing on the mun i get different results, im not good at explaining things.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nim trying to set up a triangular constelation evenly spaced at 300,000 m, i do my burns according to that tool yet my relays end up in weird orbits, like, instead of it coming out to an equalateral triangle i keep getting an \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:16px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003Eisosceles.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the author\u2019s permission and encouragement, I made this a while ago:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7849235548\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/177833-18x-ksp-resonant-orbit-calculator/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T16:03:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 dat